RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 16500. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAMIE'S LAST HOPE angled in to battle for the lead while three wide, gained command on the turn, then kicked clear of threatening rival in the early stretch and was ridden out under strong hand urge to prevail in the end. EL JOKER stalked the pace from the inside into the turn, dug in the early stretch but came up evenly and lacked the winning bid in the end. EMPERIAL EAGLES broke sharply then raced in the middle of the pack while four wide, rallied in the early stretch to close willingly but it was no enough in the end. ARBITRO settled back heading into the turn, then bid in the upper stretch while three wide and came up empty. BELLA BRISA vied for the lead early from the inside, continued to race in close to the leader throughout the turn, rallied in the upper stretch, was hard used and gave way in the end. DIM THE LIGHTS was unhurried early and no threat. CHA CHING CHARLIE bid for the lead early, then settled along the rail throughout the turn then continued to flatten out in the end . W F JAZZ CAT settled inside then slipped leaving the bend and disliked going. Race was Hand Timed.
